'''Ayyoub Bouaddi''' (born 2 October 2007) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{French football updater|Lille}} club [[Lille OSC|Lille]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|928593}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Youth career===
After starting football as a child in [[Creil]], Bouaddi joined [[Lille OSC|Lille]] academy in 2021. On 21 August 2023, he signed his first professional contract with the club until June 2026.<ref>{{cite web|title=AYYOUB BOUADDI SIGNE PROFESSIONNEL|url=https://www.losc.fr/actualites/2023-08-21/ayyoub-bouaddi-signe-professionnel|date=21 August 2023|access-date=7 October 2023}}</ref>

===Lille===
On 5 October 2023, Bouaddi made his senior debut for Lille in a [[UEFA Europa Conference League]] group stage match against Faroese club [[Klaksvíkar Ítróttarfelag|KÍ]] which ended as a goalless draw.<ref>{{cite web|title=Klaksvik - Lille : le milieu du LOSC Ayyoub Bouaddi bat deux records de précocité|url=https://www.lavoixdunord.fr/1381612/article/2023-10-05/klaksvik-lille-ayyoub-bouaddi-records-de-precocite|date=5 October 2023|access-date=7 October 2023}}</ref> At the age of 16 years and 3 days, this made him the youngest player ever to play in a European club competition game.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lille : Ayyoub Bouaddi devient le plus jeune joueur de l'histoire des Coupes d'Europe|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Lille-ayyoub-bouaddi-devient-le-plus-jeune-joueur-de-l-histoire-des-coupes-d-europe/1423660|date=5 October 2023|access-date=7 October 2023}}</ref> He also became the youngest player to appear in an official match for Lille, a record which was previously held by [[Joël Henry (footballer)|Joël Henry]] since 1978.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ayyoub Bouaddi, plus jeune joueur de l'histoire à porter les couleurs du LOSC|url=https://lepetitlillois.com/2023/10/05/ayyoub-bouaddi-plus-jeune-joueur-de-lhistoire-a-porter-les-couleurs-du-losc/|date=5 October 2023|access-date=7 October 2023}}</ref> On 22 October, at 16 years and 20 days, he became the youngest player in [[Ligue 1]] since [[:fr:Joël Fréchet|Joël Fréchet]] in 1981.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ligue 1. À 16 ans et 20 jours, le Lillois Ayyoub Bouaddi devient le plus jeune joueur du XXIe siècle|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/ligue-1/ligue-1-a-16-ans-et-20-jours-le-lillois-ayyoub-bouaddi-devient-le-plus-jeune-joueur-du-xxie-siecle-a355b65a-718a-11ee-8ee4-6d23d2858b34/|date=23 October 2023|access-date=17 March 2024}}</ref>

A year later, on 2 October 2024, Bouaddi became one of the youngest Lille players to start in a [[UEFA Champions League]] match, playing on his 17th birthday in a 1–0 home win against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase|2024–25 league phase]].<ref name="E021024">{{cite news |language=fr |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Le-real-madrid-avec-camavinga-et-endrick-mais-sans-mbappe-contre-lille-qui-titularise-le-jeune-bouaddi/1511490 |title=Le Real Madrid avec Camavinga et Endrick, mais sans Mbappé contre Lille, qui titularise le jeune Bouaddi |date=2 October 2024 |newspaper=[[L'Équipe]] |access-date=2 October 2024}}</ref> He started alongside captain [[Benjamin André]], following a series of absences in the midfield with the [[Hákon Arnar Haraldsson]], [[Ethan Mbappé]] and [[Ngal'ayel Mukau]]'s injuries, [[Angel Gomes]]' suspension, adding to [[Nabil Bentaleb]] and [[André Gomes]]' non-qualification.<ref name="E021024"/> Being one of the best players on the pitch, his performance was praised by various media.<ref>{{cite news |language=fr |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/Les-notes-de-lille-real-madrid-chevalier-royal-genesio-a-trouve-la-cle/1511571 |title=Les notes de Lille - Real Madrid : Chevalier royal, Genesio a trouvé la clé |last1=Domenighetti |first1=Joël |last2=Penot |first2=Hervé |last3=Degorre |first3=Damien |date=3 October 2024 |newspaper=[[L'Équipe]] |access-date=3 October 2024 |url-access=subscription}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |language=fr |url=https://www.lavoixdunord.fr/1508431/article/2024-10-02/les-notes-des-lillois-contre-le-real-madrid-l-epoustouflant-lucas-chevalier |title=Les notes des Lillois contre le Real Madrid : l'époustouflant Lucas Chevalier |date=2 October 2024 |newspaper=[[La Voix du Nord]] |access-date=2 October 2024 |url-access=subscription}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet |language=fr |user=lavoixdessports |number=1841593210117800201 |date=2 October 2024 |title=Lucas Chevalier impérial, Ayyoub Bouaddi sérieux... Retrouvez les notes des joueurs lillois face au Real Madrid sur notre site |access-date=2 October 2024}}</ref> After the final whistle, Lille [[ultras]] sang ''[[Happy Birthday to You|Joyeux Anniversaire]]'' (French for "Happy Birthday to You") with the players for Bouaddi when celebrating the win.<ref>{{Cite tweet |language=fr |user=losclive |number=1841598388040818788 |date=2 October 2024 |title=17 ans, 90 minutes contre le Real Madrid 🎁 𝑱𝒐𝒚𝒆𝒖𝒙 𝒂𝒏𝒏𝒊𝒗𝒆𝒓𝒔𝒂𝒊𝒓𝒆 𝑨𝒚𝒚𝒐𝒖𝒃 ❤️ |access-date=3 October 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Bouaddi has been part of France’s youth setup at various levels, including the [[France national under-21 football team|under-21 side]], which he captained.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mondial de Montaigu - Ayyoub Bouaddi buteur avec l'équipe de France U16|url=https://madeindogues.ouest-france.fr/infos/article-mondial-de-montaigu-ayyoub-bouaddi-buteur-avec-l-equipe-de-france-u16-409734.html|date=6 April 2023|access-date=7 October 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ayyoub Bouaddi, le choix fort|url=https://www.football.fr/equipe-de-france/ayyoub-bouaddi-le-choix-fort-806967.html|date=27 March 2026|access-date=26 May 2026}}</ref>

On 15 May 2026, the [[Royal Moroccan Football Federation]] announced that [[FIFA]] had approved their request to switch Bouaddi's international allegiance to Morocco.<ref>{{cite web|title=Le Maroc officialise le choix d'Ayyoub Bouaddi, ancien capitaine de l'équipe de France Espoirs, de changer de nationalité sportive|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Le-maroc-officialise-le-choix-d-ayyoub-bouaddi-ancien-capitaine-de-l-equipe-de-france-espoirs-de-changer-de-nationalite-sportive/1676204|language=fr|date=16 May 2026|access-date=26 May 2026}}</ref> On 26 May, Bouaddi was named in [[Morocco national football team|Morocco's]] 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Pour la première fois dans la liste du Maroc, Ayyoub Bouaddi ira bien à la Coupe du monde, Achraf Hakimi sélectionné lui aussi|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Pour-la-premiere-fois-dans-la-liste-du-maroc-ayyoub-bouaddi-ira-bien-a-la-coupe-du-monde-achraf-hakimi-selectionne-lui-aussi/1679130|language=fr|date=26 May 2026|access-date=26 May 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Born in France, Bouaddi is of Moroccan origin.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ayyoub Bouaddi, plus jeune joueur de l'histoire des Coupes UEFA|url=https://www.maghress.com/fr/lionsdelatlas/13384086|date=6 October 2023|access-date=7 October 2023}}</ref> In June 2023, at the [[Elysée Palace]], he won the fourth [[eloquence]] competition for French soccer academies.<ref>{{cite web|title=D'un concours d'éloquence à l'Élysée aux pelouses de Ligue 1 : Ayyoub Bouaddi, le phénomène de précocité du Losc|url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/ligue-1/dun-concours-deloquence-a-lelysee-aux-pelouses-de-ligue-1-ayyoub-bouaddi-le-phenomene-de-precocite-du-losc-17-03-2024-V4NLFZQR2JFU7LXBN756OEWAXI.php|date=17 March 2024|access-date=17 March 2024}}</ref>

